I was moved by these stories of public officers who went above and beyond to help others when the COVID-19 first hit us. Despite the challenges of dealing with multiple unknowns, fluid circumstances and personal sacrifices, they rose to the occasion and gave their best.

We have stabilised our COVID-19 situation by dint of an immense effort. As of yesterday, there were no locally transmitted cases since March. But the battle goes on. Public officers in various agencies continue to monitor developments here and abroad closely, and be ready to respond quickly and take action to support communities and businesses, and curb the spread of the virus.&nbsp;

@gov.sg worked with four local filmmakers – @relaxlahtariqq, @jonathan77, @elliengim, and K.Rajagopal – to produce these four short films, in commemoration of Public Service Week 2020. You can view them at: http://go.gov.sg/as-one&nbsp;

My heartfelt thanks to all in our Public Service for your dedication and commitment! – LHL

#PSW2020

Took part in a virtual dialogue with senior leaders across Asia&nbsp;organised by @mckinseyco this morning.

The theme was “Reimagining the next normal for Asia and the World”. I shared what we have been doing to see Singapore through this COVID-19 pandemic.&nbsp;

To wrap up our discussion, moderator Oliver Tonby, Chairman of McKinsey & Company Asia, asked for my views on good leadership.&nbsp;

My answer: a good leader must muster a capable team that you can trust, and tap on others who know more than you. You must also be psychologically prepared for surprises and setbacks, and make the best decision based on the knowledge you have. Above all, focus on your responsibilities and fulfil your duty to your people, regardless of any personal consequences to yourself. – LHL
&nbsp;
(MCI Photo by Terence Tan)

10 October is World Mental Health Day. The @WHO held an online advocacy event yesterday to raise awareness, and I shared a few words on what we are doing in Singapore.

Ensuring access to quality mental healthcare for every citizen is a major priority for us. COVID-19 has made this especially vital, as more people face stresses, pressures and disruptions to their lives and livelihoods. We’ve set up a National CARE Hotline (1800-202-6868) and a COVID-19 Mental Wellness Taskforce, to help all those who need it.

One of the biggest hurdles dealing with mental health problems is the stigma. But this is also why the best and most reliable support system is the people around us. If we know someone having a tough time, even a simple “how are you?” is a good way to show we care, and to reassure them it’s okay to talk about their problems.&nbsp;

In Singapore, 1 in 7 will suffer from a mental health condition at some point in their lives. Just as we take care of each others’ physical health by wearing masks, let us also work together to understand mental health better, to care for one another during these difficult times. – LHL
&nbsp;
(PMO Video by Alex Qiu)

Today marks 30 years of diplomatic relations between Singapore and China. Our relationship started even before formal establishment of diplomatic ties in 1990, and our bilateral collaboration has deepened and expanded over the years.
&nbsp;
China has been our largest trading partner and we have been China’s largest foreign investor since 2013. People-to-people exchanges have also grown. In 2018 more than four million people travelled between our countries – 40 times as many as the 100,000 travellers in 1990. COVID-19 has suspended the flights for now, but amid the pandemic, we have continued to support each other, and embarked on new areas of cooperation. Beyond bilateral ties, we have also worked well together in regional and international fora.
&nbsp;
I look forward to growing and strengthening our ties and bringing our partnership to greater heights. – LHL

(Premier Li Keqiang made an official visit to Singapore in November 2018. / MCI Photo by LH Goh)

Enjoyed a night of live performances with residents at the Teck Ghee Virtual Lantern Night event. Chatted with some families who had tuned in, and others who had taken part in a pre-event Snowskin Mooncake Virtual Baking Workshop.&nbsp;

My thanks to our grassroots team for their creative efforts in organising these fun activities for all to enjoy safely despite the pandemic.&nbsp;

If you missed the event, you can watch it on the Teck Ghee Facebook Page, or my Facebook Page. I hope that this time next year, we will be able to celebrate at our usual venue at Bishan-AMK Park once again.

Happy moon gazing in the week ahead, and do remember to eat those mooncakes in moderation! ;) – LHL

