Held separate virtual meetings with the advisory panels of the Economic Development Board (EDB) and the Monetary Authority of Singapore (MAS) over the past two evenings.&nbsp;

The panels comprise leaders of MNCs and financial institutions from across the globe, who advise the EDB and MAS on our strategies. Singapore has a reputation for being open and pro-business, and our regular dialogues help keep us in touch with what businesses are focused on, as well as trends we need to watch.&nbsp;

We had a lot to discuss this year – sustainability, geopolitics, US-China tensions, nationalist tendencies, and whether or not COVID-19 would result in a ‘new normal’ or ‘old ++’. Some noted that with working from home becoming a necessity, having capable island-wide technological infrastructure is one of Singapore’s advantages in a post-COVID world.&nbsp;

I am grateful to EDB and MAS, as well as all the members of both panels, for helping Singapore to keep moving forward in an uncertain world. – LHL
&nbsp;
([1] Dialogue with EDB’s International Advisory Council. / MCI Photo by Fyrol; [2] Dialogue with the MAS International Advisory Panel. / MCI Photo by Terence Tan)

