@amktowncouncil has completed its Masterplan for the next five years. I was supposed to launch it this weekend along with an exhibition, but with the tighter measures to stem the spread COVID-19, this was called off.

The pandemic has preoccupied all of us, but we cannot drop everything and wait for it to pass. As we fight COVID-19, we must continue improving our home, and keep building Singapore. This e-book (https://bit.ly/amkmasterplan) outlines our plans for Ang Mo Kio. Residents can look forward to new aquatic playgrounds, a Sports Recreation Hub, and better amenities and facilities. A copy of the book will be delivered to all AMK households.

These new plans would not be possible without the collective efforts of grassroots leaders, town councillors and advisors. Not forgetting our residents, too, for their support over the years! We may be facing dark clouds now, but I am confident that our future is bright. – LHL (Photo by me)

Took part in an Extraordinary Virtual @g20org Leaders’ Summit this evening. It was called by Saudi Arabia, holding the G20 Presidency this year, to discuss the COVID-19 pandemic. The outbreak has permeated and changed all the norms of our daily lives — including the way business is conducted.

This is a global crisis, and needs a global solution. I called on the leaders to collaborate in three areas:

1. Public health — helping one another fight the outbreak;
2. Our economies — to save businesses and our citizens’ jobs; 
3. Science and research — to find a treatment or vaccine for COVID-19, and prepare for future pandemics.

The pandemic will eventually end, but it will not be the last one the world faces. We must learn from our experiences, and emerge stronger and more resilient from them. – LHL (MCI Photo by Zinkie Aw)
